In article ffe@ccu2.auckland.ac.nz,  pgut01@cs.aukuni.ac.nz (Peter Gutmann) writes:

>The problem is that once the RFD hits news.groups, the whole proposal will 
>become swamped with shouting from about a dozen different splinter groups 
>who want a moderated sci.crypt.research, a moderated sci.crypt, a moderated 
>s.c.r and an unmoderated comp.crypt.sources, a moderated s.c.r and an 
>unmoderated s.c, no change at all because of namespace pollution, and 
>several other variants of the above.  Since every group is completely 
>convinced that their point of view is the right one, there'll never be 
>enough votes for any particular proposal to pass, because everyone else will 
>vote against it (or at least that's what people indicated in postings and 
>private mail the last time round).

Well, I'd like to see a moderated sci.crypt.research newsgroup, 
and regarding:

	> an unmoderated comp.crypt.sources

comp.sources.misc has provision for this (me!) - so there's one less problem.


				- alec

